snippet.textDisplay: My main issue concerns lower lash liner. Perhaps if I start with eyes & prime them really well, I may not have this problem. I tend to use a felt tip liner (my favorite type & it usually stays put on my top lash line) very lightly under the eye, then set it with a shadow. I use setting spray but perhaps not one strong enough. What usually happens is later in the evening, I wind up with raccoon eyes. I thank you for sharing your tips & tricks. Hope this alleviates this issue for me. Hope you & your family are having a great 2020 so far!

I do this everyday for my lashes to stay curled. I take my blowdryer on low heat and low air and AFTER I have finished with my mascara and all is done, I take the blow dryer to my closed eye and with my finger hold my lashes in a curl and blow the mascara dry.....it WILL not only keep your lashes curled all day but curl them even more. I have yet to see any beauty guru do this technique.
It WORKS !!!
I usually do one eye at a time to make sure that the mascara is wet when I blow dry
